# Environment variables

Copy to `.env` for local development (Bun loads `.env` automatically).

```bash
# HTTP
PORT=3000
CORS_ORIGIN=*

# SQLite
DB_PATH=./data/ratings.db

# Massey upstream
MASSEY_URL=https://masseyratings.com/data/json

# Secrets (CI/CD — env backend)
MASSEY_API_TOKEN=
DB_ENCRYPTION_KEY=
SECRETS_BACKEND=auto

# Scheduler — seconds between auto-refresh (0 = disabled)
REFRESH_INTERVAL=3600

# Rate limit on POST /api/ratings/refresh (per client IP)
REFRESH_RATE_LIMIT=5
REFRESH_RATE_WINDOW=60

# Protect manual refresh (Bearer or X-Refresh-Token); unset = no auth
REFRESH_TOKEN=

# Massey upstream resilience
MASSEY_TIMEOUT_MS=30000
MASSEY_RETRY_ATTEMPTS=2

# Graceful shutdown drain timeout (ms)
SHUTDOWN_TIMEOUT_MS=10000

# Structured request logging (JSON lines to stdout)
REQUEST_LOG=true

# Vault (production)
VAULT_ADDR=
VAULT_TOKEN=
```

## Bun.secrets (local dev)

```bash
bun run secret set com.bradley-terry.massey api-token "your-token"
bun run secret set com.bradley-terry.db encryption-passphrase "optional-key"
```

Namespaces map to `SecretClient.get(namespace, name)` — see [docs/ARCHITECTURE.md](ARCHITECTURE.md).
